  sodium: 3 g
  serving size: 458
---

Pour @water{300%ml}(cold, salted) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%grams} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid. Leave to cook for
~{12%minutes}.

Remove the pot from the heat and leave aside for another ~{12%minutes}, or until
ready to serve (keep covered so the rice can continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, place a pan over medium heat (without oil).

Once hot, add the @sesame seeds{1%sachet} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until
lightly toasted, ~{2-3%mins}.

Transfer the seeds from the pan and set aside (reserve the pan to use later).

> Watch the seeds like a hawk—they can burn easily.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated). Use a #teaspoon{} to scrape away the peel.

In a #large bowl{}, mix the ginger, garlic, @ketjap manis{1%sachet}, @soy sauce{1%sachet},
@BBQ rub{1%sachet}, 2 tsp @sugar{2%tsp} and half the sesame seeds. Blend to a smooth
paste with a #food processor{} if desired.

Add the @Irish beef strips{250%grams} to the bowl and allow to sit for ~{5-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

While the meat marinates, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and
thinly sliced).

Roughly chop the @mushrooms{250%grams}(roughly chopped).

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

When hot, fry the onion and mushrooms until softened, stirring occasionally,
~{4-5%mins}. Transfer from pan once cooked.

> TIP: Give the pan a wipe if you like—you'll be using it again!

Return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, fry the beef strips until browned, ~{5-7%mins}, shifting as they colour.

> IMPORTANT: Beef is safe to eat when outside is browned.

Add the onions, mushrooms, and any remaining marinade to the pan along with 25ml
@water{25%ml}.

Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if required. Season to taste with @salt{to taste}
and @pepper{to taste}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between bowls.

Top with the beef bulgogi.

Garnish with a sprinkle of scallion and the remaining sesame seeds.